 <title>New Horizon</title>
 <link>https://vse.la/matt-darey/new-horizon-0</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
          &lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;It´s been a long time&lt;br /&gt;
Since our ship set sail&lt;br /&gt;
All along the moody river&lt;br /&gt;
Until we reached out for the sea&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We were crossing miles and miles&lt;br /&gt;
We were sailing nameless fields&lt;br /&gt;
Once we lost our guiding star&lt;br /&gt;
The roaring ocean took us far away&lt;br /&gt;
Far away from here&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Heart of mine&lt;br /&gt;
Come lead me the way&lt;br /&gt;
Heart of mine&lt;br /&gt;
We won`t go astray&lt;br /&gt;
Lead me to a new horizon&lt;br /&gt;
Where all my doubts are flown away&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&#039;s quiet a long time&lt;br /&gt;
Since we are travelling on and on&lt;br /&gt;
Oh tell me can we make it through this waves?&lt;br /&gt;
In search of love and freedom&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Will we make it through a storm?&lt;br /&gt;
And sail around the swirls of ego&lt;br /&gt;
The flaming skies shall open up&lt;br /&gt;
Shall open up and carry us to land&lt;br /&gt;
And carry us to land&lt;br /&gt;
Carry us to land&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Heart of mine&lt;br /&gt;
Come lead me the way&lt;br /&gt;
Heart of mine&lt;br /&gt;
We won`t go astray&lt;br /&gt;
Lead me to a new horizon&lt;br /&gt;
Where all my doubts are flown away&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I was haunted in my soul&lt;br /&gt;
I couldn`t hear you anymore&lt;br /&gt;
What was it we were looking for?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We were walking borderline&lt;br /&gt;
Never weak, always strong&lt;br /&gt;
I fell in and out of love&lt;br /&gt;
Into the place were i belong&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Heart of mine&lt;br /&gt;
Come lead me the way&lt;br /&gt;
Heart of mine&lt;br /&gt;
We won`t go astray&lt;br /&gt;
Lead me to a new horizon&lt;br /&gt;
Where all my doubts are blown away&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
